<subsection><title>Wrap-Up</title>

<p>In this Lesson, we worked on the following skills and goals:</p><ul>

<li><p>Use ratios and rates for comparison.</p></li> 
<li><p>Compute and interpret a rate of change.</p></li>
<li><p>Interpret slope as a rate of change.</p></li>
<li><p>Illustrate slope on a graph.</p></li>
<li><p>Use the definition of slope to compute <m>\Delta y</m> or <m>\Delta x</m>.</p></li>
<li><p>Recognize a linear relationship by its constant rate of change.</p></li>
<li><p>Write a linear model using slope and initial value.</p></li></ul>

<commentary audience="instructor"><title>Questions for Writing or Discussion</title>
<p><ol>
<li><p>What do we use ratios and rates for?</p></li>
<li><p>Suppose  represents your distance from home, in miles. Compare the meanings of the two statements <m>x=30</m> and <m>\Delta x=30</m>.</p></li>
<li><p>Explain how slope measures the steepness of an incline.</p></li>
<li><p>State two useful consequences of the fact that lines have constant slope.</p></li>
</ol></p></commentary>

</subsection>
